HOW TO BUILD A DEBIAN PACKAGE FOR THE UNISIM BUILD TOOLS ?
----------------------------------------------------------

1) The short solution
---------------------

$ ./build.sh

2) The long solution:
---------------------

2.a) configure for installation in a temporary directory

$ path-to-unisim.org-svn-devel-build-tool/configure \
                                          --prefix=$HOME/tmp/unisim_1.0-1_i386/usr \
                                          --with-systemc=$HOME/systemc-2.2.0 \
                                          CPPFLAGS=-I/usr/include/libxml2 \
                                          CXXFLAGS="-O3 -g3 -DSC_INCLUDE_DYNAMIC_PROCESSES"

2.b) install in the temporary directory

$ make install

2.c) create a DEBIAN subdirectory in your temporary installation directory

$ mkdir $HOME/tmp/unisim_1.0_i386/DEBIAN

2.d) copy file "control" in that DEBIAN subdirectory

$ cp control $HOME/tmp/unisim_1.0-1_i386/DEBIAN/control

2.e) Build the debian package

$ dpkg-deb --build $HOME/tmp/unisim_1.0-1_i386

$HOME/tmp/unisim_1.0-1_i386.deb is the debian package

APPENDIX:
---------

To finding package dependencies on a binary program:
$ ./find-deps <program>
